message.content:
When vegans and vegetarians get married, they often desire a menu that aligns with their dietary preferences. Here is a sample vegetarian/vegan wedding dinner menu:

Appetizers:
1. Caprese Skewers (vegetarian) - cherry tomatoes, bocconcini cheese, fresh basil leaves; drizzled with extra virgin olive oil
2. Vegan Spring Rolls - rice paper filled with julienned vegetables and avocado, served with a soy dipping sauce

Salad Course:
3. Mixed Greens Salad (vegan) - mixed greens tossed in a citrus vinaigrette and topped with dried cranberries, sunflower seeds or candied pecans

Soup Course: 
4. Tomato Basil Bisque (can be vegan if made without cream) or Roasted Cauliflower Soup (vegan)

Main Entrees:
5a . Eggplant Parmesan Lasagna (vegetarian): layers of roasted eggplant slices instead of pasta sheets combined with marinara sauce and cheese mixture
b . Stuffed Bell Peppers (vegan) : bell peppers stuffed with quinoa mixed-vegetable pilaf spiced up featuring sundried tomato pesto on top.

Side Dishes for Main Entrees :
6a . Caramelized Balsamic-Glazed Brussels Sprouts.
b . Rosemary Garlic Mashed Potatoes/Vegan Sour Cream Garlic Mashed Yukon Gold Potatoes/Cauliflower mash.
c . Grilled asparagus/Green beans almondine seasoned lightly 

Desserts:
7a  Strawberry shortcake(buffalo milk dairy products can be subbed for vegan).
b  Seasonal fruit tarts(gluten-free). 
c   Chocolate fondue fountain w fruits(display centerpiece).
